I have recently just discovered ITZY and decided to check them out and this video made me realize they have a lot of potential in the future. These are just some of the things i wanna point out as a trained performer for 5-6 years. Starting with Yeji the leader (white top and black bottom) Shes just unbelievably incredible, shes got everything the vocal,dance, and rapping too and not gonna lie shes one of the most beautiful female kpop idols i've ever seen but im very sure they were trained to sing and dance at the same time so they must have a lot of experiences i think the main thing that i caught a lot on Yeji is her facial expressions while singing and dancing, mainly Yeji has the best facial expressions out of all the ITZY members well atleast for me but i think she needs to work more on her facial expressions while dancing and singing yes its difficult to multitask but thats the only problem i can point out for Yeji.  Lia the main vocalist (black top and bottom with a ponytail and black sneakers)  I've heard that Lia is a vocalist trained to be a dancer which i can see in this video, it shows a lot but shes not a bad dancer just lack of energy and details, her problem with dancing is she doesn't know when to extend her movements although her isolations are pretty good, facial expressions on point, with her vocals i think she needs to work on her stamina and breathing control, in here i can totally see shes struggling with belting the higher notes which is i think because its the lack of room for breathing since their choreos are on another level. Ryujin the center (Black top and bottom with blonde hair)  Personally think she has the best stage presence after Yeji I can only point out her live vocals, shes lacking a lot on stability and volume and what i mean by volume is that sometimes she sings too quiet or too loud but mostly too quiet, Ryujin is not apart of the vocal line which is understandable but maybe working on improvements for her live vocals would be great since she has an amazing vocal color and tone. Chaeryeong the main dancer (Black croptop and black bottom with a ponytail)  She is pretty similar to Yeji They've both got the vocals and dance. But her as the main dancer the only thing i can point out is her stage presence she has a great stamina but maybe she could work on her facial expressions more i see shes going for a serious attitude but i know she can do so much better with more creative expressions. One more thing is her live vocals are AMAZING. Yuna the maknae (White top and bottom with a ponytail)  She isn't apart of the vocal line but i appreciate how she belts the notes especially during her prechorus part in the first verse if we compare her to Lia you can see Lia with her part in the second verse she ended up singing in falsetto but theres nothing wrong with it but theres a huge comparison, she has the best stage presence along with Ryujin or Yeji. Please correct me if i got any of the members wrong or mixed them up I'd appreciate it because i just started stanning them â£ï¸
a year later and still the best dance practice for me, live vocals without comprimising the facial expressions and choreo

I think Lia is the type of person that has weak stamina/energy, that is why she always sounds like she is always out of breath when singing. i'm not saying she's a bad singer, her voice  has more of a low tone and she definitely sounds better when singing songs that are not too high. I think JYP chosed her to be main vocalist because her voice outstands every member when she sings in a low tone. The  fact that she still sounds very good while dancing really hard is definitely amazing, not all groups can sing this stable when dancing, especially that ITZY's choreos are really hard and fast. I believe that with more practice she'll definitely become better. Hoping that JYP will release songs that fit her more. Lia is my bias btw.

I've seen people with the same opinions with me- this is no hate to actual girls, it's literally about the choreo. And can we talk about this live performance, stability? YES. Itzy are really stepping up the game for dance practices.

They all so amazing, ITZY LIVE DAMN  ITZY LIKE IT, NOT SHY NOT ME ITZYEEE
If you think this song is about love then you're missing the point and here's why: In Korean female-male dating culture it's commonly expected that females have a more passive role in the stablishment of a relationship. Flirting, confessing their feelings to someone and asking them out is widely seen as a male role. So, in a way, females are supposed to passively wait til some guy decided to flirt with them and be asked to engage in a romantic relationship. According to an Korean friend of mine, this is something that has been changing a lot with the newer generations, but these biased gender roles still persist and are still regarded as the "convetional" behaviour. So, in Not Shy, although the girls are singing about being in love with someone, the song is more than just that. They're saying that they're confident and bad-ass enough that they can just go up to the guy and tell him how they feel and ask him out themselves. It's a song about self-confidence, independence and, dare I say,  it's somewhat of an emancipation cry. Therefore, please give Not Shy all the love it deserves and know that it's not just another generic love song. Sorry about the wall of text. Also if you made it this far, please give my comment a like so more people can see it :)

"Hard choreo" = "strong/powerful dance move" only... There are reasons why they said this is their hardest choreo to date. Look at how fast and yet detailed each movements are... There is also no time to breathe in the choreo itself ok like the split seconds at the "let the beat drop" part -- where people expect a freaking dance break there is probably the only part where they can rest for a bit after moving non-stop... It's like they legit took a break for dancing for a seconds there bc the whole song is like a freaking "dance break" lol.  Also they also need to control how hard/soft they move between each move ok... We've seen they did this with previous choreographies tbh but this one, the split moment where they have to change from one move to another, and from one spot to another are crazy fast.... And they manage to excel all those moves individually & as a group that synchronise so well with one another even with different styles of dancing...  On top of that we got a live vocal performance for this? It's crazy. You really can feel how all of them work for this ok...   That's why it's kinda sad whenever I saw some people are still complaining about stuff like this choreo is not that hard, it's a disappointment bc there's no dance break, etc2... oh well... I still see lots and lots of people are praising them too so I hope the girls can focus on those good stuff instead if they ever saw the netizens comments.  :)

tips for online classes ( an actual thread )  1. wake up at the same time you would on a normal school day!  â€¢ making a routine and setting a time to wake up will make it easier to focus and work â€¢ waking up early will give you plenty of time to get work done earlier.  â€¢ making a routine might also help you feel better!  2. take notes the same way you would in class  â€¢ you can look back at them during tests or quizzes, or if you simply don't understand something  â€¢ just because nobody can see your notes doesn't mean they won't be useful.  3. ask if you don't understand something!  â€¢ send emails, texts, call, ask during online classes; if you have a question, ASK it! classes online can be confusing and your teacher will understand that, don't be shy!  4. put your phone/other electronics away  â€¢ act like the teacher is in the room with you; don't check your phone, silence it, don't let it distract you.  â€¢ sometimes having a show/video playing in the background is nice, but it can get distracting; focus on class instead!  5. FOCUS!  â€¢ it can be really hard to focus since it feels like there's no consequences for not paying attention: THERE ARE! stay focused and get your work done as soon as you can! focus as hard as possible.  6. try not to cheat on tests  â€¢ it can be really easy to cheat on tests and quizzes since there's nobody who can see you doing it, but when school starts again, you won't be able to do that; try not to cheat ( though if you do i can't blame you-)  7. take breaks  â€¢ give yourself breaks throughout the day! the benefit of online classes is that you can create your own schedule. if you wanna take a break for literally an HOUR, do it! (make sure you're still getting work done, though)  8. don't stress  â€¢ i promise you everyone is just as worried about this as you are; it's normal to feel worried. don't be afraid to ask for help if anxiety is making it impossible to focus  9. take care of yourself, too.   â€¢ if online school is starting to deteriorate your mental health, talk to someone about it, preferably your teacher so you guys can work something out.  â€¢ if you need help with your mental health, ask for it. you aren't alone.  10. attend your zoom/video classes.   â€¢ i know it sounds like a drag to sit in front of a camera for hours listening to your teacher, but it'll end up being beneficial. attend your zoom classes people!!  11. do your work in an environment with no distractions  â€¢ don't do it in bed, in the living room or kitchen, etc. because you'll definitely get distracted. try setting up a desk somewhere in a nice, clean room where you won't be able to get distracted by anything/anyone.  12. don't skip meals and drink plenty of water  â€¢ you'll focus better on a full stomach; listen to your body and don't overwork yourself â€¢ it's been scientifically proven that water helps your brain focus better! drink plenty of it.  13. ask your friends if you're confused  â€¢ chances are they're doing some of the same classes as you! if you don't wanna ask a teacher, you can always ask them.  14. try to get outside at least once a day  â€¢ take a break from school to go on a walk, sit outside for a bit, etc. it'll be refreshing.  and finally, 15. put yourself first.  â€¢ school doesn't matter if your mental health is deteriorating or if you're doing bad; put yourself first. talk to people, reach out for help, and make sure you're doing okay. there is so much help out there and you're never alone, i promise.

The confidence and statement this video exudes is just so awesome. But it DOES open them up to criticism (which is expected but let's try to be diplomatic about it).  Lia has improved so much with her live singing, but she seems like she needs some help learning how to belt high notes because she scrunches up her face every time which means it's really hard for her. I love her lower register here though.   Yeji and Ryujin's rap delivery strength is so well controlled!  Yeji, Yuna, and Chaeryeong also sing with like...restrained/tight voices rather than doing it like Twice's Jihyo or GG's Taeyeon (sounds very open), or even Lia (she sings great, it's just the high notes that are hard). Yuna sounds like a kid too, but I mean SHE IS A KID so no big deal =)) It sounds like she sings with the back of her tongue stuck to her throat.  JYPE vocalists aren't always the best (I give that recognition to SME vocalists, those dudes know how to TRAIN lol), so I kinda get it, but at least help your artists!  Disclaimer: I'm no vocal coach so idk what the terms are. I just go by what I hear, but kudos to ITZY for doing their best every time.
